<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<!--
  Optional prompt enchantments add ONE extra "important context:" line to selected
  first-person diary prompts. Most text comes from the live hediff's game label, body part,
  urgency bucket, and strongest impact cues; important-event-only DLC status sources can also add
  the pawn's royal title or ideoligion role. This XML only controls which sources are eligible and
  how often they win.

  Tuning fields:
    chance / frequency  - per-prompt appearance chance after matching, 0..1. frequency is an alias.
    weight              - relative random weight when several enchantments pass their chance roll.
    severity            - multiplier for weight; use it to make urgent health states win more often.

  Hediff severity tiers:
    hediffSeverityTiers may override chance/frequency/weight/severity for visible matching hediffs.
    Levels are XML-tuned in DiaryTuningDef.xml (defaults: minor >= 0.05, moderate >= 0.25,
    major >= 0.50, critical >= 0.75). The highest configured level at or below the live severity wins.

  hediffDefNames are plain strings and fail silently when absent, so DLC/modded content can be
  mentioned without making the whole mod depend on it.
-->
